Creating a ROS2 Package

Command:
ros2 pkg create my_robot_controller --build-type ament_python --dependencies rclpy

What it does:
Creates a new ROS2 package named **my_robot_controller**.

Requirements:

* ROS2 installed
* Workspace created (ros2_ws)
* Inside the **src** folder of workspace

Meaning of options:

ros2 pkg create
→ command to create a new ROS2 package

my_robot_controller
→ name of the package

--build-type ament_python
→ package will use Python

--dependencies rclpy
→ adds ROS2 Python client library dependency

Where to run:

cd ~/ros2_ws/src
ros2 pkg create my_robot_controller --build-type ament_python --dependencies rclpy
